steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"2t14d","text":"Place the dried down peptides into the drawer in B2071, either in a labelled bag (\u003c20), or box if you are submitting a large batch of samples.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1l5sv","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1ttn2","text":"On the label, you must include ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"djici","text":"PPMS order number (not project), ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"1h854","text":"number of samples, ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2bphb","text":"and any other important details, such as run length, ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"38dj9","text":"sample manifest (i.e. which order you wish the data to be acquired in, if minimization of carryover is important),","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"bold","offset":7,"length":8}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"eabkv","text":"and whether the samples have been prepared in S-trap lysis buffer, or another buffer (e.g. urea, triton etc). ","type":"unordered-list-item","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"3medc","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"22a42","text":"Don’t forget to include your lab group/PI, as this is the folder within which your data files will be stored on the server.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"9qi6","text":" ","type":"atomic","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"6pmd7","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"notes","mutability":"IMMUTABLE","data":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[{"length":11,"offset":0,"style":"bold"}],"key":"bvv4f","text":"Manifests: Go to PPMS, and prepare a manifest relating to the samples, pay particular attention to the run order that you would like. ","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"4f8po","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"5ie7d","text":"Any analytical technique will suffer from a degree of sample carryover, LC-MS is no different.","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"8np46","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"203k4","text":"For example, if you have knockdown/knockout samples, it is recommended that you run these before your WT/control samples. ","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"faga6","text":"","type":"unstyled"},{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"96b0f","text":"Add in the position of the blanks/standards that you would like to see in the acquisition of your data, we usually add these between every five to six samples. ","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}}}}}
